There are a few interesting observation from above pair plot that:¶

Campaign (number of contacts made) with clients who have approx. mode balance amount with bank deposits were made majorly not with those who were outliers (Very high or no balance).¶

Duration of the call is also higher for clients who have approx. mode balance amount with bank deposits were made majorly not with those who were outliers (Very high or no balance).¶

pdays (number of days past) are lower for clients who have approx. mode balance amount with bank deposits were made majorly not with those who were outliers (Very high or no balance).¶

Observed correlation between Duration, Campaign and pdays with balance

Replacing the Categories: education, default, housing, loan, poutcome and Target as Ordered variables; and job, marital, contact and month as one hot encoding¶

In [10]:
replaceStruct ={
    "education":{"primary": 1,"secondary": 2,"tertiary": 3,"unknown": -1},
    "default": {"no":0,"yes":1},
    "housing":{"no":0,"yes":1},
    "loan":{"no":0,"yes":1},
    "poutcome":{"failure":0,"success":1,"other":2,"unknown":-1},
    "Target":{"no":0,"yes":1}
}
oneHotCols =["job","marital","contact","month"]
In [11]:
bankdata = bankdata.replace(replaceStruct)
bankdata = pd.get_dummies(bankdata, columns = oneHotCols)

Comparison of models¶

This classification problem is about Banking Indusry with a target to classify the clients as term deposit subscribers or not. We have to understand the context here and then decide on the best model: In our task. as to identify the clients to target for Term Deposit subscriber, we have to not miss on the any plausible client. In this case we can say that Cost of opportunity very high. the cost of oportunity (that is cost of loosing an at Personal Loan customer) is much lesser as compared to Cost of defult (means givg loan to a defaulter)

Hence, in view of the above, simple accuracy measure may not be the right measure for a good clssifier. We will look at the high Recall for our model, that is out of all actual positives, how many have been identify correcty by our models. The more Recall is better in our case.

Model 1: Logistic Regression : Recall = TP/ (TP+FN) = 172/(172+1379) = 0.11

Ensemble learning with LR: Recall = TP/ (TP+FN) = 167/(167+1384) = 0.11

Model 2: KNN: Recall = TP/ (TP+FN) = 190/(190+1361) = 0.12

Ensemble learning with KNN: Recall = TP/ (TP+FN) = 165/(165+1386) = 0.11

Model 3: Naive Bayes: Recall = TP/ (TP+FN) = 660/(660+ 811) = 0.45

Ensemble learning with NB: Recall = TP/ (TP+FN) = 667/(667+ 884) = 0.43

Model 4: Decision Tree: Recall = TP/ (TP+FN) = 11850/(11850 + 163) = 0.986

Ensemble learning(Random Forest): Recall = TP/ (TP+FN) = 11756/(11756+ 257) = 0.98                

Grdient Boosting: Recall = TP/ (TP+FN) = 260/(260+ 1291) = 0.16                

Ensemble learning (Bagging): Recall = TP/ (TP+FN) = 405/(405 + 1146) =  0.26

Hence seeing the above results, Decision Tree is the favored model probably the reason being that our data has lots of outliers whichmight have influenced the performance of other models.
